# SWT dashboard live event stream (per-session JSONL emitted by the CLI;
# session-local state, not project artifact).
#
# Also ignore `.swt-planning/`: the dashboard's Init flow creates
# `.swt-planning/PROJECT.md` + `STATE.md` in the daemon's cwd, which during
# local development of SWT itself is the source repo root. SWT v3 development
# uses `.vbw-planning/` (VBW-driven), so `.swt-planning/` here is always
# dev-test detritus and should never enter git. When SWT-on-SWT dogfooding
# lands, this entry needs revisiting.
.swt-planning/
# Exception: test-utils fixtures (v2-baseline for the migration boot-clean
# test + future v3-baseline parity recordings) are intentional, committed
# golden artefacts. Plan 06-04 T1 (REQ-19).
!packages/test-utils/golden/**/.swt-planning/
!packages/test-utils/golden/**/.swt-planning/**

# Changesets internals
.changeset/.changes-*/

# Local research artefact (kept out of git unless intentionally added)
compass_artifact_*.md

# Local working copy of VBW (out of git; not part of SWT)
vibe-better-with-claude-code-vbw-main/

# Non-production scratch / experiment files (anywhere in the tree, all
# current and future contents). Keep out of git so the repo stays
# focused on shippable code.
non_production_files/

# --- VBW planning state (fully local as of 2026-05-12) ---
#
# `.vbw-planning/` is **fully gitignored** — planning artifacts
# (PROJECT.md, REQUIREMENTS.md, ROADMAP.md, STATE.md, phase plans,
# summaries, research, and the VBW runtime state) are LOCAL ONLY.
# Earlier policy tracked them on v3-foundation; the 2026-05-12 main-
# only pivot retired that branch and the workspace is now treated as
# Claude Code session scratch, not a shared planning surface.
#
# Historical commits still resolve to the previously-tracked content
# via git's blob history — only the working-tree visibility changes.
# Public commit messages and CHANGELOG entries reference plan
# numbering (PR-NN) which stays meaningful; the plan files themselves
# stay on the local machine of whoever's driving the session.
.vbw-planning/

# TDD3 working doc (transposition spec — never committed)
TDD3.md

# Vendored VBW methodology scripts — regenerated by
# scripts/internal/port-from-vbw.sh from
# a_non_production_files/vibe-better-with-claude-code-vbw-main/scripts/.
# Not tracked in git; the porter is the single source of truth.
scripts/*
# Carve out the porter itself (SWT-owned automation, not VBW asset).
!scripts/lib/
scripts/lib/*
!scripts/internal/
!scripts/internal/port-from-vbw.sh
# Carve out SWT-owned scripts (pre-port, not VBW assets).
!scripts/bump-version.sh
!scripts/check-bundle-size.mjs
!scripts/check-offline.mjs
!scripts/docs-gen.ts
!scripts/public-benchmark.mjs
!scripts/record-cassette.mjs
